Class Delivery

java.lang.Object
  com.teama.pds.ActionNode
      com.teama.pds.Delivery

public class Delivery
extends ActionNode

Author: Grant Kurtz The Delivery controller keeps the fleet of vehicles that move all orders from the store to the colleges. It assigns orders to vehicles for delivery and holds the orders until a vehicle returns for pick-up.

                               throws AlreadyInstantiatedException
Keeps the requirement of only allowing one Delivery station to be operated at any given point in time. This method may only be called exactly once.

Parameters:
time - The object that will accurately report time information
dest - The HashMap of destination locations
avail_trucks - The inbox that will hold all trucks currently waiting or returning to the pizza shop
outbound - The trucks that are leaving the Pizza Shop and going to their destination to deliver pizzas.
orders - The orders that are waiting to be delivered and completed.
Returns:
an already initialized instance of this class, or creates a new one if this is the first time this class is being created.
Throws:
AlreadyInstantiatedException - This is thrown if this method has already been called.
